What is an exception in Java?
a) A syntax error
b) A runtime error
c) A logical error
d) A compilation error

Which keyword is used to handle exceptions in Java?
a) try
b) catch
c) throw
d) all of the above

What is the purpose of the "finally" block in a try-catch-finally statement?
a) To catch exceptions
b) To specify the code that always executes, whether an exception occurs or not
c) To throw an exception
d) To declare exceptions

Which of the following is a checked exception in Java?
a) NullPointerException
b) ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException
c) IOException
d) IllegalArgumentException

