a) The program will terminate
b) The exception will be ignored
c) The program will continue executing the code outside the "try" block
d) It is a compilation error

Can you have multiple catch blocks for a single try block?
a) Yes
b) No

What is the purpose of the "throws" clause in a method signature?
a) To declare that the method may throw exceptions
b) To handle exceptions within the method
c) To catch exceptions thrown by other methods
d) To specify the return type of the method

Which of the following is not a subclass of the Throwable class in Java?
a) Error
b) Exception
c) RuntimeException
d) String

